Ivory Coast’s Ouattara to Review Gbagbo-Era Army Promotions

-- B y   P a u l i n e   B a x
-- 
2011-06-16T11:51:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-16/ivory-coast-s-ouattara-to-review-gbagbo-era-army-promotions.html
Ivory Coast  President Alassane Ouattara will set up a committee of senior military officials to
review army promotions awarded under ex-leader  Laurent Gbagbo ’s
regime, according to a government statement.  The committee, headed by Defense Minister  Guillaume Soro ,
is to “review the appointments and promotions of officers and
soldiers of rank, and address the anomalies,” according to an e-
mailed statement yesterday.  It will comprise six army generals, including chief of
staff Philippe Mangou, the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pauline Bax in Abidjan via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 